      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 7,
      "message": "we will need to add configuration for the category.\n\nOne way to do it would be to copy BE-configuration.yaml.erb to the integation test dir, add config for the category. I would suggest the following as config:\n\n  TEST service:\n    required: true\n    baseTypes:\n      - tosca.nodes.nfv.testNodeComplex\n    doNotExtendBaseType: true\n\n\nand mount it to the backend in the docker plugin, e.g.:\n\n<volume>${project.basedir}/BE-configuration.yaml.erb:/app/jetty/chef-solo/cookbooks/sdc-catalog-be/templates/default/BE-configuration.yaml.erb</volume>\n\n\nIm open to other suggests if there is another way to do it",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5269,
        "name": "Michael Morris",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
        "username": "MichaelMorris"
